[
  [
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "(** * Varieties of function extensionality *)",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Require Import HoTT.Basics HoTT.Types.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Require Import Metatheory.Core.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Local Open Scope path_scope.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n(** In the Overture, we defined function extensionality to be the assertion that the map [apD10] is an equivalence.   We now prove that this follows from a couple of weaker-looking forms of function extensionality.  We do require eta conversion, which Coq 8.4+ has judgmentally.\n\n   This proof is originally due to Voevodsky; it has since been simplified by Peter Lumsdaine and Michael Shulman. *)\n\n(** Naive funext is the simple assertion that pointwise equal functions are equal.  The domain and codomain could live in different universes; the third universe argument is essentially the max of [i] and [j] (and similarly for all subsequent axioms). *)\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Definition NaiveFunext :=\n  forall (A : Type@{i}) (P : A -> Type@{j}) (f g : forall x, P x),\n    (forall x, f x = g x) -> (f = g).",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n(** Naive non-dependent funext is the same, but only for non-dependent functions.  *)\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Definition NaiveNondepFunext :=\n  forall (A B : Type) (f g : A -> B),\n    (forall x, f x = g x) -> (f = g).",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n(** Weak funext says that a product of contractible types is contractible. *)\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Definition WeakFunext :=\n  forall (A : Type) (P : A -> Type),\n    (forall x, Contr (P x)) -> Contr (forall x, P x).",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n(** The obvious implications are\n   [Funext -> NaiveFunext -> WeakFunext] and [NaiveFunext -> NaiveNondepFunext].\n   None of these do anything fiddly with the universes either. *)\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Definition Funext_implies_NaiveFunext@{i j max}\n  : Funext_type@{i j max} -> NaiveFunext@{i j max}.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": [
        {
          "_type": "goal",
          "name": null,
          "conclusion": "Funext_type -> NaiveFunext",
          "hypotheses": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Proof.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": [
        {
          "_type": "goal",
          "name": null,
          "conclusion": "Funext_type -> NaiveFunext",
          "hypotheses": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "intros fe A P f g h.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": [
        {
          "_type": "goal",
          "name": null,
          "conclusion": "f = g",
          "hypotheses": [
            {
              "_type": "hypothesis",
