    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Definition NaiveFunext_implies_NaiveNondepFunext@{i j max}\n  : NaiveFunext@{i j max} -> NaiveNondepFunext@{i j max}\n  := fun nf A B f g => nf A (fun _ => B) f g.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n(** The non-obvious directions are that [WeakFunext] implies Funext and that [NaiveNondepFunext] implies [WeakFunext] (and hence all four are logically equivalent). *)\n\n(** ** [WeakFunext] implies [Funext] *)\n\n(** To show that [WeakFunext] implies Funext, the point is that under weak funext, the space of \"pointwise homotopies\" has the same universal property as the space of paths. *)\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Section Homotopies.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Context (wf : WeakFunext).",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Context {A:Type} {B : A -> Type}.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Context (f : forall x, B x).",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n  (* Recall that [f == g] is the type of pointwise paths (or \"homotopies\") from [f] to [g]. *)\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Let idhtpy : f == f := fun x => idpath (f x).",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n  (** Weak funext implies that the \"based homotopy space\" of the Pi-type is contractible, just like the based path space. *)\n  (** Use priority 1, so we don't override [Contr Unit]. *)\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "#[export] Instance contr_basedhtpy : Contr {g : forall x, B x & f == g } | 1.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": [
        {
          "_type": "goal",
          "name": null,
          "conclusion": "Contr {g : forall x : A, B x & f == g}",
          "hypotheses": [
            {
              "_type": "hypothesis",
              "names": [
                "wf"
              ],
              "body": null,
              "type": "WeakFunext"
            },
            {
              "_type": "hypothesis",
              "names": [
                "A"
              ],
              "body": null,
              "type": "Type"
            },
            {
              "_type": "hypothesis",
              "names": [
                "B"
              ],
              "body": null,
              "type": "A -> Type"
            },
            {
              "_type": "hypothesis",
              "names": [
                "f"
              ],
              "body": null,
              "type": "forall x : A, B x"
            },
            {
              "_type": "hypothesis",
              "names": [
                "idhtpy"
              ],
              "body": "fun x : A => 1",
              "type": "f == f"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Proof.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": [
        {
          "_type": "goal",
          "name": null,
          "conclusion": "Contr {g : forall x : A, B x & f == g}",
          "hypotheses": [
            {
              "_type": "hypothesis",
              "names": [
                "wf"
              ],
              "body": null,
              "type": "WeakFunext"
            },
            {
              "_type": "hypothesis",
              "names": [
